description: Two new reports warn of Russian disinformation and potential cyberattacks targeting the Paris Olympics, less than two months before the summer games begin. NBC News' Keir Simmons reports.
title: New warnings of Russian threats to Paris Olympics

description: Three days after President Biden urged Hamas to accept an Israeli peace deal, Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu took issue with Mr. Biden's description of the Israeli offer, saying the war won't end unless Hamas is destroyed and the hostages are released. NBC News' Raf Sanchez reports.
title: Netanyahu says war won't end unless Hamas is destroyed

description: An alarming new report from Microsoft says Russia is trying to scare people away from 2024 Olympics in Paris by stoking fears of terrorism and also trying to discredit the International Olympic Committee. Russia was banned from the Olympics because of its invasion of Ukraine.
title: Report says Russia is trying to scare people away from attending the Olympics

description: Beijing has accused two Chinese citizens of spying for Britain, in the latest test of a relationship that has grown increasingly fraught.
title: Beijing accuses 2 Chinese citizens of being British spies

description: Claudia Sheinbaum was headed for a landslide victory to become Mexico's first female president and vowed to follow the programs of her mentor and outgoing leader, Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador, whose popularity among the poor helped drive Sheinbaum's win.
title: Claudia Sheinbaum makes history as the first woman elected president of Mexico

description: Dozens of parachutists jumped from aircraft dating back to World War II as part of commemorations marking the 80th anniversary of the D-Day landings.
title: Parachutists leap from WWII-era planes over Normandy to help mark D-Day's 80th anniversary
